Package grafioschtrader.service

Class GTNetHistoricalImportService

java.lang.Object
grafioschtrader.service.BaseGTNetExchangeService
grafioschtrader.service.GTNetHistoricalImportService
@Service public class GTNetHistoricalImportService extends BaseGTNetExchangeService
Service for importing historical price data from GTNet peers after security creation. This service orchestrates the historical data import workflow:
  1. Query coverage metadata from all eligible GTNet peers (message code 85)
  2. Select the best peer based on coverage length and success rate
  3. Fetch historical data from the selected peer (message code 80)
  4. Fall back to connector if GTNet peers don't have data

    • selectBestPeer

      public GTNetHistoricalImportService.PeerSelection selectBestPeer(Map<GTNet,HistoryquoteCoverageResponseMsg> coverageByPeer, String isin, String currency)
      Selects the best peer for fetching historical data based on coverage and success rate. Selection criteria:
      1. Coverage length: Days from minDate to maxDate (longer = better)
      2. Success rate: Based on past exchange logs (currently not weighted)
      3. Priority: Based on consumerUsage configuration (lower = better)
      Parameters:
      coverageByPeer - map of peer to coverage response
      isin - the ISIN to look up
      currency - the currency to look up
      Returns:
      the best peer selection, or null if no peer has coverage
